-- Telenor Indicates VimpelCom's Orascom Price May Need Revising, FT Reports
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2010-10-15T01:11:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/telenor-indicates-vimpelcom-deal-price-may-need-to-be-revised-ft-reports.html
Telenor ASA , VimpelCom Ltd.’s
second-biggest shareholder, has indicated that the price
VimpelCom is paying to acquire most of  Naguib Sawiris ’s telecoms
assets may have to be revised, the Financial Times reported,
citing Telenor’s Chief Executive Officer  Jon Fredrik Baksaas .  The agreement may have to be changed if the Algerian
government moves to nationalize Orascom Telecom Algeria, Baksaas
said, according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ben Martin  in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net . 